rom educational history, critical race theory, first-year writing studies, Africana studies, African American cultural theory, cultural materialism, narrative inquiry, and basic writing scholarship. Connections between social justice, language rights, and new literacies are uncovered from the vantage point of a multiracial, multiethnic Civil Rights Movement.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aAfrican AmericansxEducation. 0aAfrican AmericansxSocial conditions. 0aEnglish languagexComposition and exercisesxStudy and teachingzUnited States. 0aEnglish languagexRhetoricxStudy and teachingzUnited States. 0aMulticultural educationzUnited States. 4aAfrican American Studies : African American Studies. 4aEducation : English Education. 4aEducation : Higher Education. 4aLanguage Arts : Composition and Rhetoric Studies. 7aEDUCATION / Multicultural Education.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438446370423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438446370/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles